## Memory System

> Persistent memory with Learning Loop — see docs/LEARNING-LOOP.md

### Available Commands

| Command | Action | Learning Loop Stage |
|---------|--------|---------------------|
| `resume` | Pull + load last handoff | — |
| `remember <slug>` | Save a memory entry using the remember command | 1. CAPTURE |
| `recall <keyword>` | Search memory using the recall command | 2. APPLY (pre) |
| `apply <memory>` | Bump applied_count + announce using the apply command | 2. APPLY |
| `audit` | Run a session health report using the audit command | 4. EVOLVE |
| `promote <memory>` | Graduate a memory entry to the agent identity file | 5. PROMOTE |
| `handoff` | Audit + save + commit + push using the handoff command | 4. EVOLVE |

> **Note for codex-compatible tools**: Commands above are built-in commands provided by the agent framework. Invoke them directly (e.g., `remember <slug>`) rather than as slash commands.

### Proactive Memory — AUTO

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| New session start | Read `memory/latest-handoff.md` — summarize before starting |
| Important decision | Save to memory immediately — category: `decision` |
| Reusable pattern found | Save to memory immediately — category: `pattern` |
| Mistake or friction | Save to memory immediately — category: `lesson` |
| User says "remember this" | Save to memory immediately — category per content |
| End of session | Run handoff immediately |
| Starting work on known topic | Search memory first — check for existing context |

### Memory Storage

```
memory/
├── MEMORY.md                    <- Index (Map of Content)
├── _promotions.md               <- Promotion audit trail
├── _template/                   <- Memory file templates
│   ├── feedback-template.md
│   └── pattern-template.md
├── latest-handoff.md            <- Shortcut to latest handoff
└── YYYY-MM/                     <- Monthly folders
    └── YYYY-MM-DD-{type}-{slug}.md  <- Memory entries
```

